{"article_id":"GgfoRu6lh4mK50W1","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"One of the more important conservative beliefs about Obamacare ,","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"running right alongside the certainty","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"that the law is a disaster","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"that will fail in every respect ,","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"is the belief","depth":3},{"id":5,"text":"that Americans share their antipathy to the law .","depth":3},{"id":6,"text":"It certainly is true that the Affordable Care Act has a bad reputation ,","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"and the latest poll","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"showing","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"that support for Obamacare has dipped","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"prompted the same wave of conservative gloating","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"that results from every such poll .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"But looking even an inch beneath the surface reveals a public more frustrated and confused by Obamacare","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"than opposed .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"Its specific elements poll well ,","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"though they ' re the least known elements .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"Four out of ten Americans don ' t realize","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"the law hasn ' t been struck down .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"A new poll out shows","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"that the public , by a ten-point margin , trusts Democrats over Republicans on health-care issues .","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"By a 52-34 percent margin , they want Congress to implement or tinker with the law","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"rather than repeal it .","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"The nearly ubiquitous conservative belief","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"that the public shares its passion","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"for repealing Obamacare","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"is a spate of self-delusion .","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"That overconfident delusion is the subject of Ramesh Ponnuru ' s long National Review essay","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"pleading with conservatives to stop believing their own bullshit .","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Ponnuru faithfully affirms the general outlines of the right-wing case :","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"Of course the law is terrible ,","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"of course it won ' t work ,","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"of course it must be repealed .","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"He even repeats the misleading line","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"that Max Baucus warned","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"the law would be a \" train wreck. \"","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"But Ponnuru gently warns","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"that the failure might be slow to arrive ,","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"and perhaps not the Greece-esque national catastrophe","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"conservatives have talked themselves into expecting .","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"His account of what conservatives expect to happen ,","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"furnished from within the movement ,","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"is actually frightening :","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"A few conservative lawmakers have speculated","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"that the law will crash so badly","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"that the Democrats will themselves demand repeal in the next couple of years .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"A few Republicans","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"who believe","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"that these effects should not be put off :","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"that Americans should suffer them","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"so as to see the failure of Obamacare with their own eyes .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"Only then will they turn against the law and its supporters with the requisite passion","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"to undo it .","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"Ponnuru argues","depth":4},{"id":53,"text":"that Republicans must also get serious , finally , about replacing the law with something other than the status quo .","depth":4},{"id":54,"text":"But there ' s a reason","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"Republicans don ' t make repealing Obamacare contingent on an alternative plan :","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"Alternative plans","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"that do anything","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"are hard .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"People get attached to what they have and suspicious of change .","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"Republicans killed Bill Clinton ' s health reform","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"by raising the specter","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"that people","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"who have insurance","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"would get something different ,","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"which they didn ' t trust .","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"The GOP ' s only real health-care traction in the 2012 elections came","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"by assailing Obama","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"for cutting Medicare .","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"Republicans have wisely decided to attack Obamacare","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"without committing themselves to an alternative","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"because the alternative would be easy to attack .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"Ponnuru , for instance , suggests","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"changing the tax code and stripping regulations","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"to create \" a market","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"in which almost everyone would be able to purchase relatively cheap , renewable insurance policies","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"that protected them from the risk of catastrophic health expenses. \"","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"Telling tens of millions of Americans","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"they ' ll lose their insurance","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"that covers basic medical expenses","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"and get bare-bones policies with thousands of dollars in deductibles","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"is not a winning play .","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"The Republican war against the implementation of Obamacare is largely an attempt","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"to exploit Amercians ' aversions to change .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"That ' s why the GOP is throwing around wild , inflated claims of \" rate shock \"","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"- sowing fears","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"that Obamacare will jack up peoples ' health-insurance premiums .","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"The latest party organ","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"to do this","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"is the Republican leadership in Ohio ,","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"which is warning its citizens","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"that they will face enormous new costs .","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"( Jonathan Cohn takes apart the shoddy claims . )","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"The tiny kernel of truth is that a handful of people","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"- mostly young , male , and healthy -","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"will have to buy into some kind of regular insurance plan","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"that covers stuff , not only plans","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"that cover your costs","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"if you ' re injured in a car crash","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"and make you pay for just about everything else .","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"The scare campaign could work , at least to some extent .","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"But","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"if it works ,","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"it won ' t work","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"because Americans are dying to be converted to an all-catastrophic , high-deductible system .","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"What Republicans have going for them is that health care is really complicated ,","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"people don ' t spend hours a day","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"boning up on public policy ,","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"and those","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"who have insurance","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"understandably fear losing what they have .","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"But the vast majority of the public is not going to see any changes under the new law .","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"Even if the Obamacare exchanges collapse ,","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"they only bring in people","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"who don ' t have Medicare or employer coverage anyway","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"and are already suffering through a dysfunctional individual insurance market .","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"The \" shock \" is going to be felt by conservatives","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"who are expecting their Randian fantasies of socialist dystopia to come true .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":235,"left":123,"right":234,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":121,"right":122,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":121,"left":0,"right":120,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":1,"right":119,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":234,"left":168,"right":233,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":168,"left":138,"right":167,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":134,"right":137,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":134,"left":128,"right":133,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":128,"left":6,"right":127,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":125,"right":126,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":125,"left":7,"right":124,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":126,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":129,"right":132,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":130,"right":131,"relation":"explanation"